#exercise 5: take the following python code that stores a string

# Write code using find() and string slicing (see section 6.10) to extract the number at the end of the line below. 
# Convert the extracted value to a floating point number and print it out.

法一：
（课堂所学）
text = "X-DSPAM-Confidence:    0.8475"
pos=text.find(':')
snum=text[pos+1:]
fnum=float(snum.strip())
print(fnum)
print(type(fnum))

法二：
（.split）
text = "X-DSPAM-Confidence:    0.8475"
num=text.split(' ')[-1]
print(num)

法二-1（完善）：
text = "X-DSPAM-Confidence:    0.8475"
a=text.split(' ')
n=0
for i in a:
    n+=1
    try :
        num=float(i)
        print(num)
    except:
        pass



法三：
text = "X-DSPAM-Confidence:    0.8475"
num=text[-6:]
print(num)

法四：
（filter）
#filter(function, iterable)
#function -- 判断函数。
#iterable -- 可迭代对象。
python2 可用filter
python3 要import re

text = "X-DSPAM-Confidence:    0.8475"
import re
text= re.sub("\D", "",text)
print(text)
结果：08475（小数点“.”没了）

str.isdigit 无法保留小数点?




